wlsxSwitchMIB.name: wlsxSwitchMIB
wlsxSwitchMIB.contactinfo: Postal: 1322 Crossman Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: dl-support@arubanetworks.com Phone: +1 408 227 4500
wlsxSwitchMIB.description: This MIB module defines MIB objects which provide System level information about the Aruba switches.

wlsxSwitchIp.name: wlsxSwitchIp
wlsxSwitchIp.description: Switch IP as configured by the user. This IP address uniquely identifies the switch.

wlsxSwitchRole.name: wlsxSwitchRole
wlsxSwitchRole.description: Role of this switch in the Switch Domain.

wlsxSwitchListTable.name: wlsxSwitchListTable
wlsxSwitchListTable.description: This Table will list all the switches in the Switch Domain. It will be populated only on the master switch. Local switches return empty table.

wlsxSwitchLicenseCount.name: wlsxSwitchLicenseCount
wlsxSwitchLicenseCount.description: The number of licenses installed on the switch

wlsxSwitchLicenseTable.name: wlsxSwitchLicenseTable
wlsxSwitchLicenseTable.description: This table lists all licenses installed on the switch.

licenseFlags.name: licenseFlags
licenseFlags.description: License flags; E - enabled; A - auto-generated; R - reboot required to activate

licenseService.name: licenseService
licenseService.description: The service enabled by this license.

wlsxSysXProcessorTable.name: wlsxSysXProcessorTable
wlsxSysXProcessorTable.description: The table of processors contained by the switch.

wlsxSysXProcessorEntry.name: wlsxSysXProcessorEntry
wlsxSysXProcessorEntry.description: An entry for one processor contained by the switch.

sysXProcessorLoad.name: sysXProcessorLoad
sysXProcessorLoad.description: The average, over the last minute, of the percentage of time that this processor was not idle.

wlsxSysXStorageTable.name: wlsxSysXStorageTable
wlsxSysXStorageTable.description: The table of Storage-devices contained by the switch.

wlsxSysXStorageEntry.name: wlsxSysXStorageEntry
wlsxSysXStorageEntry.description: An entry for one long-term storage device contained by the switch.

sysXStorageSize.name: sysXStorageSize
sysXStorageSize.description: size of the storage filesystem in MB.

sysXStorageUsed.name: sysXStorageUsed
sysXStorageUsed.description: size of the storage filesystem in MB.

wlsxSysXMemoryTable.name: wlsxSysXMemoryTable
wlsxSysXMemoryTable.description: The memory status of the switch

wlsxSysXMemoryEntry.name: wlsxSysXMemoryEntry
wlsxSysXMemoryEntry.description: An entry for one memory region on the switch. Currently, only the CP region is monitored.

wlsxSwitchLicenseSerialNumber.name: wlsxSwitchLicenseSerialNumber
wlsxSwitchLicenseSerialNumber.description: The license serial number of the switch

wlsxSwitchUserTable.name: wlsxSwitchUserTable
wlsxSwitchUserTable.description: This Table lists all the users (both wired and wireless) currently connected to the switch. Users are identified by their IP address.

userIpAddress.name: userIpAddress
userIpAddress.description: IP Address from which the user connected to the switch.

userPhyAddress.name: userPhyAddress
userPhyAddress.description: Physical Address of the station from which the user connected to the switch.

userRole.name: userRole
userRole.description: The Role configured for this user.

userUpTime.name: userUpTime
userUpTime.description: Time since the user is connected to the switch.

userAuthenticationMethod.name: userAuthenticationMethod
userAuthenticationMethod.description: Authentication mechanism used by the user to connect to the switch.

userLocation.name: userLocation
userLocation.description: Location of the access point (in Building.Floor.... format), which the user used to connect to the switch.

userServerName.name: userServerName
userServerName.description: Name of the Back-end authentication server, used to authenticate the user.

userConnectedVlan.name: userConnectedVlan
userConnectedVlan.description: Vlan on which the user is connected to the switch.

userConnectedSlot.name: userConnectedSlot
userConnectedSlot.description: Slot on switch, where the user connection terminates.

userConnectedPort.name: userConnectedPort
userConnectedPort.description: Port on switch, where the user connection terminates.

userBWContractName.name: userBWContractName
userBWContractName.description: Name of the Bandwidth Contract applied to this user.

userBWContractUsage.name: userBWContractUsage
userBWContractUsage.description: Indicates how the Bandwidth Contract is used.

userConnectedModule.name: userConnectedModule
userConnectedModule.description: The module to which the user is connected, if wired.

wlsxSwitchStationMgmtTable.name: wlsxSwitchStationMgmtTable
wlsxSwitchStationMgmtTable.description: This Table lists all the wireless stations associated with the Access points connected to this switch.

staPhyAddress.name: staPhyAddress
staPhyAddress.description: The Physical Address of the Station.

staAccessPointBSSID.name: staAccessPointBSSID
staAccessPointBSSID.description: BSSID of the Access point through which the station is connected to the switch

staUserName.name: staUserName
staUserName.description: Name of the User connecting from this station.

staAssociationID.name: staAssociationID
staAssociationID.description: AID with which the Station is associated with this system.

staTransmitRate.name: staTransmitRate
staTransmitRate.description: Indicates Transmit rate of the channel

staReceiveRate.name: staReceiveRate
staReceiveRate.description: Indicates Receive rate of the channel

wlsxSwitchStationStatsTable.name: wlsxSwitchStationStatsTable
wlsxSwitchStationStatsTable.description: This Table lists the statistics of all the wireless stations associated with the Access points connected to this switch.

staTxPackets.name: staTxPackets
staTxPackets.description: Total Packets Transmitted by the station.

staTxBytes.name: staTxBytes
staTxBytes.description: Total Bytes Transmitted by the station.

staRxPackets.name: staRxPackets
staRxPackets.description: Total Packets Received by the Station

staRxBytes.name: staRxBytes
staRxBytes.description: Total Bytes Received by the station.

staBwRate.name: staBwRate
staBwRate.description: Bandwidth Rate in Kbps of the station.

staFrameNonUnicastRate.name: staFrameNonUnicastRate
staFrameNonUnicastRate.description: Station Frame Non Unicast Packet Rate.

wlsxSwitchTotalNumAccessPoints.name: wlsxSwitchTotalNumAccessPoints
wlsxSwitchTotalNumAccessPoints.description: Total Number of Access Points Connected to this switch.

wlsxSwitchTotalNumStationsAssociated.name: wlsxSwitchTotalNumStationsAssociated
wlsxSwitchTotalNumStationsAssociated.description: Total Number of Stations Associated to this switch.

wlsxSwitchAccessPointTable.name: wlsxSwitchAccessPointTable
wlsxSwitchAccessPointTable.description: This Table lists all the Access Points Connected to this switch.

apBSSID.name: apBSSID
apBSSID.description: The Physical Address of the Access Point.

apSlot.name: apSlot
apSlot.description: Slot to which the Access Point is connected.

apPort.name: apPort
apPort.description: Port to which the Access Point is connected.

apPhyType.name: apPhyType
apPhyType.description: Physical Layer Protocol support of the AP.

apType.name: apType
apType.description: Indicates whether the Access point is an Air Monitor or regular AP.

apLocation.name: apLocation
apLocation.description: Location of the AP defined in Building.Floor.... mode.

apTotalTime.name: apTotalTime
apTotalTime.description: Time since the Ap is connected to the switch

apInactiveTime.name: apInactiveTime
apInactiveTime.description: Time since the Ap has been inactive

apLoadBalancing.name: apLoadBalancing
apLoadBalancing.description: Indicates whether Load balancing is enabled or not.

apChannelNoise.name: apChannelNoise
apChannelNoise.description: Indicates the noise on the channel

apTransmitRate.name: apTransmitRate
apTransmitRate.description: Indicates Transmit rate of the channel

apReceiveRate.name: apReceiveRate
apReceiveRate.description: Indicates Receive rate of the channel

wlsxSwitchGlobalAPTable.name: wlsxSwitchGlobalAPTable
wlsxSwitchGlobalAPTable.description: This Table lists all the Access Points Connected in the Switch Domain. This table is valid only on a Master switch. On a Local switch, the table is empty.

globalAPLocation.name: globalAPLocation
globalAPLocation.description: Physical Location of the AP, defined in Building.Floor.Location format.

globalAPLocalSwitch.name: globalAPLocalSwitch
globalAPLocalSwitch.description: IP Address of the Local Switch this Access Point is connected to.

globalAPdot11aPhyAddr.name: globalAPdot11aPhyAddr
globalAPdot11aPhyAddr.description: Physical Mac address of the module supporting dot11a in the Access Point. AP can have support for both dot11a and dot11b physical layer.

globalAPdot11bPhyAddr.name: globalAPdot11bPhyAddr
globalAPdot11bPhyAddr.description: Physical Mac address of the module supporting dot11b in the Access Point. AP can have support for both dot11a and dot11b physical layer.

globalAPState.name: globalAPState
globalAPState.description: State of the AP. 1 -- AP is UP. 2 -- AP is DOWN. 3-7 -- Values are deprecated.

globalAPdot11gPhyAddr.name: globalAPdot11gPhyAddr
globalAPdot11gPhyAddr.description: Physical Mac address of the module supporting dot11g in the Access Point. AP can have support for both a,b,g physical layer.

wlsxSwitchAccessPointStatsTable.name: wlsxSwitchAccessPointStatsTable
wlsxSwitchAccessPointStatsTable.description: This Table lists the statistics of all the Access Points Connected to this switch.

apStatsChannel.name: apStatsChannel
apStatsChannel.description: Channel on which the ap is operating.

apChannelBwRate.name: apChannelBwRate
apChannelBwRate.description: Bandwidth Rate in Kbps of the apChannel.

apChannelFrameLowSpeedRate.name: apChannelFrameLowSpeedRate
apChannelFrameLowSpeedRate.description: Ap Channel Frame Low Speed Rate.

apChannelFrameNonUnicastRate.name: apChannelFrameNonUnicastRate
apChannelFrameNonUnicastRate.description: Ap Channel Frame Non Unicast Packet Rate.

apChannelFrameReceiveErrorRate.name: apChannelFrameReceiveErrorRate
apChannelFrameReceiveErrorRate.description: Ap Channel Frame Receive Error Rate.

apBSSTxPackets.name: apBSSTxPackets
apBSSTxPackets.description: Total Packets Transmitted by the ap on this BSSID.

apBSSTxBytes.name: apBSSTxBytes
apBSSTxBytes.description: Total Bytes Transmitted by the ap on this BSSID.

apBSSRxPackets.name: apBSSRxPackets
apBSSRxPackets.description: Total Packets Received by the ap on this BSSID

apBSSRxBytes.name: apBSSRxBytes
apBSSRxBytes.description: Total Bytes Received by the ap on this BSSID.

apBSSBwRate.name: apBSSBwRate
apBSSBwRate.description: Bandwidth Rate in Kbps of the ap on this BSSID.

apBSSFrameRetryRate.name: apBSSFrameRetryRate
apBSSFrameRetryRate.description: Frame Retry Rate on this BSSID.

apBSSFrameLowSpeedRate.name: apBSSFrameLowSpeedRate
apBSSFrameLowSpeedRate.description: Frame Low Speed Rate on this BSSID.

apBSSFrameNonUnicastRate.name: apBSSFrameNonUnicastRate
apBSSFrameNonUnicastRate.description: Frame Non Unicast Packet Rate on this BSSID.

apBSSFrameFragmentationRate.name: apBSSFrameFragmentationRate
apBSSFrameFragmentationRate.description: Frame Fragmentation Rate on this BSSID.

apBSSFrameReceiveErrorRate.name: apBSSFrameReceiveErrorRate
apBSSFrameReceiveErrorRate.description: Frame Receive Error Rate on this BSSID.

wlsxAuthServerName.name: wlsxAuthServerName
wlsxAuthServerName.description: This Object is used in the traps to indicate the Authentication Server, used for Authentication.

wlsxAuthServerTimeout.name: wlsxAuthServerTimeout
wlsxAuthServerTimeout.description: This Object is used in the traps to indicate the Authentication Server Timeout.

wlsxFanNumber.name: wlsxFanNumber
wlsxFanNumber.description: This Object is used in the traps to indicate a failing fan number.

wlsxLineCardNumber.name: wlsxLineCardNumber
wlsxLineCardNumber.description: This Object is used in the traps to indicate a Line Card in the switch.

wlsxVoltageType.name: wlsxVoltageType
wlsxVoltageType.description: This Object is used in the traps to indicate the type of the voltage.

wlsxVoltageValue.name: wlsxVoltageValue
wlsxVoltageValue.description: This Object is used in the traps to indicate the voltage value in Float.

wlsxTemperatureValue.name: wlsxTemperatureValue
wlsxTemperatureValue.description: This Object is used in the traps to indicate Temperature Value.

wlsxProcessName.name: wlsxProcessName
wlsxProcessName.description: This Object is used in the traps to indicate a process name.

wlsxStationMacAddress.name: wlsxStationMacAddress
wlsxStationMacAddress.description: The Physical Address of the Station.

wlsxStationBlackListReason.name: wlsxStationBlackListReason
wlsxStationBlackListReason.description: The Reason for which a station is black listed.

wlsxSpoofedIpAddress.name: wlsxSpoofedIpAddress
wlsxSpoofedIpAddress.description: This Object is used in a trap to identify a Spoofed IP Address.

wlsxSpoofedOldPhyAddress.name: wlsxSpoofedOldPhyAddress
wlsxSpoofedOldPhyAddress.description: This Object is used in a trap to identify a Old Mac Address.

wlsxSpoofedNewPhyAddress.name: wlsxSpoofedNewPhyAddress
wlsxSpoofedNewPhyAddress.description: This Object is used in a trap to identify a New Mac Address.

wlsxDBName.name: wlsxDBName
wlsxDBName.description: This Object is used in a trap to identify name of the Database.

wlsxDBUserName.name: wlsxDBUserName
wlsxDBUserName.description: This Object is used in a trap to identify name of the Database user.

wlsxDBIpAddress.name: wlsxDBIpAddress
wlsxDBIpAddress.description: This Object is used in a trap to identify the IpAddress of the DB.

wlsxDBType.name: wlsxDBType
wlsxDBType.description: This Object is used in a trap to identify the Port of the user.

wlsxVrID.name: wlsxVrID
wlsxVrID.description: This Object contains the Virtual Router Identifier.

wlsxVrMasterIp.name: wlsxVrMasterIp
wlsxVrMasterIp.description: This Object contains the Master IP address.

wlsxVrrpOperState.name: wlsxVrrpOperState
wlsxVrrpOperState.description: This Object represents the VRRP operational state.

wlsxApTxPower.name: wlsxApTxPower
wlsxApTxPower.description: This Object contains the value of the AP Transmit Power.

wlsxESIServerGrpName.name: wlsxESIServerGrpName
wlsxESIServerGrpName.description: This Object represents the External Services Interface (ESI) Server Group name

wlsxESIServerName.name: wlsxESIServerName
wlsxESIServerName.description: This Object represents the External Services Interface (ESI) Server name

wlsxESIServerIpaddress.name: wlsxESIServerIpaddress
wlsxESIServerIpaddress.description: This Object represents the External Services Interface (ESI) Server IP Address

wlsxLicenseDaysRemaining.name: wlsxLicenseDaysRemaining
wlsxLicenseDaysRemaining.description: This Object represents number of the days remaining prior to a license expiry

wlsxSlotNumber.name: wlsxSlotNumber
wlsxSlotNumber.description: This Object is used in the traps to indicate a Line Card in the switch. This value matches the value of sysExtCardSlot.

wlsxSwitchIPChanged.name: wlsxSwitchIPChanged
wlsxSwitchIPChanged.description: A trap which indicates that the switch IP address has changed.

wlsxSwitchRoleChange.name: wlsxSwitchRoleChange
wlsxSwitchRoleChange.description: A trap which indicates that the role of the switch has changed in the Domain.

wlsxUserEntryCreated.name: wlsxUserEntryCreated
wlsxUserEntryCreated.description: A trap which indicates that a New user is created.

wlsxUserEntryDeleted.name: wlsxUserEntryDeleted
wlsxUserEntryDeleted.description: A trap which indicates that a user is deleted.

wlsxUserEntryAuthenticated.name: wlsxUserEntryAuthenticated
wlsxUserEntryAuthenticated.description: A trap which indicates that a user is Authenticated.

wlsxUserEntryDeAuthenticated.name: wlsxUserEntryDeAuthenticated
wlsxUserEntryDeAuthenticated.description: A trap which indicates that a user is Deauthenticated.

wlsxUserAuthenticationFailed.name: wlsxUserAuthenticationFailed
wlsxUserAuthenticationFailed.description: A trap which indicates that a user authentication has failed.

wlsxAuthServerReqTimedOut.name: wlsxAuthServerReqTimedOut
wlsxAuthServerReqTimedOut.description: A trap which indicates that the authentication server request timed out.

wlsxAuthServerTimedOut.name: wlsxAuthServerTimedOut
wlsxAuthServerTimedOut.description: A trap which indicates that the authentication server timed out.

wlsxAuthServerIsUp.name: wlsxAuthServerIsUp
wlsxAuthServerIsUp.description: A trap which indicates that the authentication server is up.

wlsxAuthMaxUserEntries.name: wlsxAuthMaxUserEntries
wlsxAuthMaxUserEntries.description: A trap which indicates that the User Entries table is full and cannot add any more entries.

wlsxAuthMaxAclEntries.name: wlsxAuthMaxAclEntries
wlsxAuthMaxAclEntries.description: A trap which indicates that the Acl Entries table is full and cannot add any more entries.

wlsxAuthMaxBWContracts.name: wlsxAuthMaxBWContracts
wlsxAuthMaxBWContracts.description: A trap which indicates that the switch reached the maximum number of configurable Bandwidth contracts.

wlsxPowerSupplyFailure.name: wlsxPowerSupplyFailure
wlsxPowerSupplyFailure.description: A trap which indicates that the power supply has failed.

wlsxFanFailure.name: wlsxFanFailure
wlsxFanFailure.description: A trap which indicates that the fan has failed.

wlsxOutOfRangeVoltage.name: wlsxOutOfRangeVoltage
wlsxOutOfRangeVoltage.description: A trap which indicates that the switch received out of range voltage.

wlsxOutOfRangeTemperature.name: wlsxOutOfRangeTemperature
wlsxOutOfRangeTemperature.description: A trap which indicates that the Temperature is out of bounds.

wlsxLCInserted.name: wlsxLCInserted
wlsxLCInserted.description: A trap which indicates that a Line card is inserted.

wlsxSCInserted.name: wlsxSCInserted
wlsxSCInserted.description: A trap which indicates that a supervisory card is inserted.

wlsxGBICInserted.name: wlsxGBICInserted
wlsxGBICInserted.description: A trap which indicates that a GBIC is inserted in a line card.

wlsxProcessDied.name: wlsxProcessDied
wlsxProcessDied.description: A trap which indicates that a process has died.

wlsxProcessExceedsMemoryLimits.name: wlsxProcessExceedsMemoryLimits
wlsxProcessExceedsMemoryLimits.description: A trap which indicates that a process is consuming large amounts of memory.

wlsxLowOnFlashSpace.name: wlsxLowOnFlashSpace
wlsxLowOnFlashSpace.description: A trap which indicates that the switch is running low on flash space.

wlsxLowMemory.name: wlsxLowMemory
wlsxLowMemory.description: A trap which indicates that the system free memory is low.

wlsxFanTrayRemoved.name: wlsxFanTrayRemoved
wlsxFanTrayRemoved.description: A trap which indicates that the fan tray is removed.

wlsxFanTrayInserted.name: wlsxFanTrayInserted
wlsxFanTrayInserted.description: A trap which indicates that the fan tray is removed.

wlsxLCRemoved.name: wlsxLCRemoved
wlsxLCRemoved.description: A trap which indicates that a Line card is removed.

wlsxSCRemoved.name: wlsxSCRemoved
wlsxSCRemoved.description: A trap which indicates that a supervisory card is removed.

wlsxPowerSupplyMissing.name: wlsxPowerSupplyMissing
wlsxPowerSupplyMissing.description: A trap which indicates that the power supply is missing.

wlsxAccessPointIsUp.name: wlsxAccessPointIsUp
wlsxAccessPointIsUp.description: A trap which indicates that an Access point at Location apLocation and Address apIpAddress is up.

wlsxAccessPointIsDown.name: wlsxAccessPointIsDown
wlsxAccessPointIsDown.description: A trap which indicates that an Access point at Location apLocation and Address apIpAddress is down.

wlsxCoverageHoleDetected.name: wlsxCoverageHoleDetected
wlsxCoverageHoleDetected.description: A trap which indicates that an Access point at Location apLocation and Address apIpAddress has detected a Coverage Hole.

wlsxChannelChanged.name: wlsxChannelChanged
wlsxChannelChanged.description: A trap which indicates that an Access point at Location apLocation and Address apIpAddress has changed the channel to apCurrentChannel.

wlsxStationAddedToBlackList.name: wlsxStationAddedToBlackList
wlsxStationAddedToBlackList.description: A trap which indicates that a station with address wlsxStationMacAddress is black listed for wlsxStationBlackListReason reason.

wlsxStationRemovedFromBlackList.name: wlsxStationRemovedFromBlackList
wlsxStationRemovedFromBlackList.description: A trap which indicates that a station with address wlsxStationMacAddress is removed from black list.

wlsxIpSpoofingDetected.name: wlsxIpSpoofingDetected
wlsxIpSpoofingDetected.description: A trap indicating that the switch detected IP Spoofing.

wlsxDBCommunicationFailure.name: wlsxDBCommunicationFailure
wlsxDBCommunicationFailure.description: A trap to indicate that communication with Database failed.

wlsxVrrpStateChange.name: wlsxVrrpStateChange
wlsxVrrpStateChange.description: A trap which indicates that VRRP State has changed on the switch.

wlsxAPRadioAttributesChanged.name: wlsxAPRadioAttributesChanged
wlsxAPRadioAttributesChanged.description: A trap which indicates changes in the Radio attributes of an Access Point at location apLocation and address apIpAddress. Ap channel is apCurrentChannel, and Transmit power is apTxPower.

wlsxESIServerUp.name: wlsxESIServerUp
wlsxESIServerUp.description: A trap which indicates that a ESI server <wlsxESIServerName> in group <wlsxESIServerGrpName> with <wlsxESIServerIpaddress> is up

wlsxESIServerDown.name: wlsxESIServerDown
wlsxESIServerDown.description: A trap which indicates that a ESI server <wlsxESIServerName> in group <wlsxESIServerGrpName> with <wlsxESIServerIpaddress> is down

wlsxLicenseExpiry.name: wlsxLicenseExpiry
wlsxLicenseExpiry.description: A trap which indicates that one or more licenses on the switch will expire in <wlsxLicenseDaysRemaining> days
